When I was meeting with the producers of The Ellen Show before my interview, they asked me if there was any particular segment from the show I loved or wanted to do. My only response was “I just want to dance with @sir_twitch_alot “. During commercial break, I couldn’t contain how excited I was to be dancing beside him on the tv, even just for a few seconds virtually. For almost a decade I’ve looked to up to this man as a dancer and one who clearly lived life loud and joyfully. tWitch is a legend and his talent, energy and legacy will not be forgotten by the millions of us he has entertained and inspired for decades. 🪩💔

No mountain hiked, no plane taken, no town ventured, no culture explored matters more than my relationship with Jesus. I’m so grateful for my church @trinitynewyork and mentor/friend/pastor @kristen.wilkerson for hosting the first ever @churchgirlconf and giving me the opportunity to dive deeper into Gods word and love for us while surround by incredible, strong women. I know church has been traumatizing for a lot of people, and there are a lot of ideas of what you need to “be” or “act like” in order to go to church or be loved by God, which I’m here to tell you is NOT true and not Jesus’ message to us… and even I, who has gone to church my whole life, was uncomfortable at first with the idea of being labeled a “Church Girl” because of this. But @churchgirlconf is all about redefining what that means and equipping women in today’s culture and I’m so excited and grateful for it. If you’re having a tough time imagining a place where you are loved and welcomed as you are, please visit my sweet fam @trinitynewyork online or in Harlem, NYC - also dm me I love talking about my faith and I’m happy to help in any way I can 🤍

I loved you. I fought for you. I DEFENDED you. And you made me look like a fool. Your pretty lights & hot cocoa & Love Actually truly made me believe you were magical in December. You KNEW I hated the cold but you did it anyway. How dare you take away my energy, my hope in men, 2 phones, my warmth and my will to live. I don’t know how I’ll feel in the future but for I need some space to focus on myself. I hope you figure things out you grow into the city I KNOW you can be. But for right now, we’re done. 💔
